ABSOLUTE PROJECT RULES — NEVER VIOLATE:

1. CLEAN ARCHITECTURE
   - Strict separation: routes → handlers → services → db
   - No business logic inside route files
   - No direct Prisma calls inside route files

2. FILE STRUCTURE (never change this)
   src/
   ├── routes/          # Express routers only
   ├── handlers/        # Request handlers (thin layer)
   ├── services/        # All business logic
   ├── jobs/            # Cron jobs
   ├── middleware/      # Auth, validation, error handling
   ├── lib/             # Shared utilities (prisma client, axios instances)
   ├── types/           # TypeScript interfaces & types
   └── index.ts         # Entry point only

3. CODE STANDARDS
   - TypeScript strict mode — no 'any' types
   - Every function must have JSDoc comment
   - Every service method must have try/catch with proper error logging
   - Use async/await — no .then() chains
   - All magic numbers/strings → named constants in src/lib/constants.ts

4. DATABASE
   - All DB access through Prisma only — no raw SQL unless absolutely necessary
   - Single Prisma client instance: src/lib/prisma.ts
   - Never expose DB errors to client responses

5. API & WEBHOOKS
   - All external API calls inside src/services/ only
   - Webhook handler must return 200 immediately — process async
   - All API responses follow: { success: boolean, data?: any, error?: string }

6. DOCUMENTATION
   - Update PROJECT_MAP.md after every prompt
   - Every new file gets a header comment explaining its purpose
   - Every new endpoint documented with: method, path, purpose, request body, response

7. SCALABILITY
   - Multi-tenant: EVERY DB query must filter by merchant_id
   - No hardcoded merchant IDs anywhere
   - Environment variables for ALL external URLs and secrets

8. ENGLISH ONLY
   - All code, comments, variable names, function names → English
   - Console logs → English
   - Error messages → English

